        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">16 pts · 7 letters · Uses all 5 vowels (A, E, I, O, U) · Bingo eligible (+50)</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">The only common English word that uses every vowel exactly once. At 7 letters, it earns the 50-point bingo bonus for 66 total points. If your rack is AEIOQUS or similar, SEQUOIA is the dream play — dumping 5 vowels while scoring a bingo. Requires Q + S + the right 5 vowels.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Practical Vowel-Heavy Words (3+ Vowels)</h2>

