          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Dump 3+ vowels per play:</span> Don't settle for playing just one vowel at a time (IT, AT, ON). Use ADIEU (4 vowels), AUDIO (4 vowels), or OURIE (4 vowels) to clear your rack fast. One good vowel dump now beats three mediocre plays later.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">QUEUE needs planning:</span> At 14 points, QUEUE is excellent — but it requires Q + two U's + two E's. If you have Q on a vowel-heavy rack without U, QUEUE isn't happening. Know your alternatives: QI (11 pts) dumps Q without needing U-heavy setups.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Accept lower scores to fix your rack:</span> Playing ADIEU for 6 points while dumping 4 vowels is often better than playing a 12-point word that only uses 1 vowel. The improved rack next turn will earn back the difference and more.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
